{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Preprocessing\n",
    "\n",
    "The ``datasets`` module contains support for a selection of state-less sample-wise preprocessing functions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import wildboar as wb\n",
    "import matplotlib.pylab as plt\n",
    "from wildboar.datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "from wildboar.datasets import preprocess"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Currently, ``wildboar`` support the following preprocessing functions:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "dict_keys(['standardize', 'normalize', 'minmax_scale', 'maxabs_scale', 'truncate'])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "preprocess._PREPROCESS.keys()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To exemplify, we can load a dataset. Note that the ``GunPoint`` dataset in the ``wildboar/ucr`` repository has already been standardized with zero mean and unit standard deviation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"GunPoint\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Instead, in the example we preprocess the samples to be in the range ``min``, ``max``. By default, the ranges form ``minmax_scale`` is set to ``0``and ``1``."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_standardized = preprocess.minmax_scale(x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7f9bf87ed430>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(x[0])\n",
    "plt.plot(x_standardized[0])\n",
    "plt.legend([\"original\", \"scaled\"])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can also supply the preproccessing function directly to the ``load_dataset`` function using the ``preprocess`` parameter."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[<matplotlib.lines.Line2D at 0x7f9c4898c2e0>]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x_standardized, y = load_dataset(\"GunPoint\", preprocess=preprocess.minmax_scale)\n",
    "plt.plot(x[0])\n",
    "plt.plot(x_standardized[0])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we can specify the ``preprocess`` argument as a string. The names are given by the ``_PREPROCESS.keys()``."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_standardized, y = load_dataset(\"GunPoint\", preprocess=\"minmax_scale\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Truncate\n",
    "\n",
    "Sometimes, when dealing with multivariate time series, we have a data where each sample is desribed by unequal-length dimensions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"SpokenArabicDigits\", repository=\"wildboar/ucrmts\")\n",
    "x = x[0:25, :3, :] # we only retain the first 3 dimensions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can use ``wildboar.iseos`` (*is end-of-sequence*) to determine if an index has the *end-of-sequence* value. Then we find the first index of that is *end-of-sequence* and, for each dimension, plot the length of that dimensions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x432 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def plot_dim_len(x):\n",
    "    eos = wb.iseos(x).argmax(axis=2)\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(nrows=eos.shape[1], figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "    cmap = plt.get_cmap(lut=eos.shape[1])\n",
    "    for dim in range(eos.shape[1]):\n",
    "        eos[eos[:, dim] == 0] = x.shape[-1] # if eos == n_timestep\n",
    "        ax[dim].scatter(\n",
    "            np.arange(eos.shape[0]),\n",
    "            eos[:, dim],\n",
    "            label=\"dim %d\" % dim,\n",
    "            marker=\"x\",\n",
    "            color=cmap(dim),\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    fig.legend(loc=\"lower left\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_dim_len(x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since many algorithms in ``wildboar`` only support dimensions and samples of uniform length, we can preprocess the time series using the ``truncate`` function. The returned time series have uniform length. Please note that truncating is very crude and result in data loss."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x432 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot_dim_len(preprocess.truncate(x))"
   ]
  }
 ],
